  "text": "A college student named Mia started getting food deliveries she never ordered. At first, it was funny. One night: ramen. Next night: bubble tea. Then groceries. Every order had the same note: 'Don’t forget to eat.' Mia thought it was her boyfriend being sweet. He said, 'What deliveries?' The orders were paid for by someone named Mia Chen. Her exact name. Her exact apartment. But the phone number was different. So Mia called it. Across the room, inside her locked closet, a phone started ringing. She froze. Then the delivery app pinged again: 'Your driver is arriving.' A second later, there was a knock. Mia looked through the peephole. No driver. Just a paper bag on the floor. Inside was her student ID. The one she had lost three years ago. And a note: 'I’ve been taking care of you longer than you think.'",
  "segments": [
